Your reasoning appears to be:

1. Different needs exist (guidance vs protection)
2. Different functions are required to fulfill those needs
3. Therefore, different supporting agents must exist
4. Hence, no single unified mechanism is sufficient

This forms a **multi-role necessity argument**.

